  "visual_description": "Two diagrams depicting the regulation of actin remodeling in dendritic spines. Image 1 shows the localization of actin-regulatory proteins (e.g., Profilin, Drebrin, Cofilin, Arp2/3) and myosin motors within a dendritic spine and its post-synaptic density (PSD). Image 2 illustrates a complex signaling pathway connecting surface receptors (EphA, EphB, N-Cadherin, NMDAR) to downstream GTPases (Rho, Rac, Cdc42) that regulate actin remodeling and spine morphogenesis, involving various kinases and GEFs (e.g., Cdk5, CaMKII, Kal7, Tiam1, DOCK180).",
